# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# peace-os .gitignore
# This file tells git what to NEVER track, even if accidentally added.
# It is the single most important safety file in a public repo.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ===== SECRETS & CREDENTIALS (the "act as me" stuff — NEVER commit) =====
# API keys, tokens, passwords live in environment variables / platform
# credential stores, NOT in the repo.
.env
.env.*
*.env
env/
secrets/
secret/
credentials/
*credential*.json
*-credentials.json
service-account*.json
*service-account*.json
gcp-key*.json
google-credentials*.json
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
auth.json
config.secret.*


# ===== CLIENT DATA (must stay in private Google Drive, NEVER in the repo) =====
# Real client brand kits, scripts, assets, campaigns — none of this is public.
clients/
client-data/
client_data/
brand-kits/
brand_kits/
assets/
uploads/
campaigns/
# Block common client media file types anywhere in the repo
*.mp3
*.mp4
*.mov
*.wav
*.m4a
*.aac
# (If you ever NEED a sample media file in the repo for a demo,
#  put it in a folder called  demo-assets/  and see the exception
#  at the bottom of this file.)


# ===== NODE / REMOTION build junk =====
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
.pnpm-debug.log*
package-lock.json.bak
dist/
build/
out/
.cache/
.remotion/


# ===== RENDER OUTPUT (generated videos — don't commit, they're huge) =====
output/
renders/
rendered/
*.rendered.mp4


# ===== n8n =====
# n8n workflow JSON exports are SAFE to commit (credentials are stored
# separately by n8n, not inside the workflow file) — so they are NOT
# ignored here. But block any local n8n database/runtime files:
.n8n/
n8n-data/


# ===== OS / EDITOR noise =====
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*~


# ===== EXCEPTION (optional) =====
# If you deliberately want ONE fake/sample media file in the repo for a
# demo (e.g. a placeholder voice note for "Billy's Burger"), uncomment
# the lines below to allow a single demo-assets folder through:
#
# !demo-assets/
# !demo-assets/**
#
# Only ever put FAKE / placeholder data in demo-assets — never a real client.
